quest_title: Consider a parallel plate capacitor of capacity 10 \(\mu\)F with air filled in the gap between plates. Now one half of the space between the plates is filled with a dielectric of dielectric constant \({K}\) = 4 as shown in figure. The capacitance of the capacitor will be
explanation_txt:
The arrangement is equivalent to three capacitors in parallel.

\(C_{1}=\cfrac{\varepsilon_{0} \cfrac{A}{4}}{d}=\cfrac{10}{4}=2.5 \mu \mathrm{F}\)

\(C_{2}=\cfrac{K \varepsilon_{0} \cfrac{A}{2}}{d}=4 \times \cfrac{10}{2}=20 \mu \mathrm{F}\)

\(C_{3}=\cfrac{\varepsilon_0 \cfrac{A}{4}}{d}=\cfrac{10}{4}=2.5 \mu \mathrm{F}\)

\(\therefore \, C_p = C_1 + C_2 + C_3 \)

\(\quad C_{p}=2.5+20+2.5=25 \mu \mathrm{F}\)

quest_title: The number of solutions of the equation \(z ^ { 2 } + \overline { z } = 0\) is
explanation_txt:
\( z =x + iy \Rightarrow \overline{z} = x -iy \)

Given equation can be written as:

\( (x+iy)^2 + x - iy = 0 \\ x^2 +2xy i -y^2 + x -iy = 0 \\ (x^2 - y^2+x) + (2xy - y) i = 0 \\ x^2-y^2+x = 0 \text {and } y(2x-1) = 0 \)

Second equation implies \( y =0\) or \(x = 1/2 \)

\( y = 0 \) in first equation gives \( x = 0 \) or \( x = -1 \).

\( x = 1/2 \) in first equation gives \( y = \pm \cfrac {\sqrt{3}}{2} \)

So there are four solutions in total: \( (0,0), (-1,0), (1/2 , \cfrac {\sqrt{3}}{2} ) \) and \( (1/2 , -\cfrac { \sqrt{3}}{2} ) \)

quest_title: A moving body of mass m and velocity 3 km/h collides with a rest body of mass 2m and sticks to it. Now the combined mass starts to move. What will be the combined velocity
explanation_txt:
Initial momentum = m x 3 + 2m x 0 = 3m

Final momentum =3m x V

By the law of conservation of momentum

\(3 m = 3 m \times V \Rightarrow V = 1 k m / h\)

Rate of heat conduction in second rod \(R_{2}=\cfrac { Q _ { 2 } } { t } = \cfrac { K A ( 150 - 110 ) } { 0.8 }\)

\(\cfrac{R_{1}}{R_{2}}=\cfrac{\cfrac { K A ( 90 - 60 ) } { 0.6 }}{\cfrac { K A ( 150 - 110 ) } { 0.8 }}=1\)
